<section style="padding: 4rem 0;">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">What are Islands?</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        Islands are interactive components that exist within a sea of static HTML. Unlike traditional
        Single Page Applications (SPAs) that ship large JavaScript bundles for every page, islands
        allow you to add interactivity only where it's needed.
      </p>

      <div style="background: #f0f9ff; border: 1px solid #0ea5e9; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        <h3 style="color: #0c4a6e; margin-bottom: 1rem;">üèùÔ∏è The Islands Architecture</h3>
        <p style="color: #075985; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          Think of your webpage as an ocean of static HTML with small islands of interactivity scattered throughout.
          Each island is self-contained and loads its own JavaScript only when needed.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem;">Benefits of Islands</h3>

      <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        <div style="background: #f9fafb; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #10b981;">
          <h4 style="color: #065f46; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">‚ö° Faster Initial Load</h4>
          <p style="color: #4b5563;">
            Static content loads instantly without waiting for JavaScript. Only interactive components
            load their JavaScript when needed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background: #f9fafb; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #3b82f6;">
          <h4 style="color: #1e40af; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">üéØ Progressive Enhancement</h4>
          <p style="color: #4b5563;">
            Your site works perfectly without JavaScript, then enhances with interactivity where needed.
            This provides a better experience for all users.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background: #f9fafb; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;">
          <h4 style="color: #92400e; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">üì± Better Mobile Performance</h4>
          <p style="color: #4b5563;">
            Reduced JavaScript means less CPU usage, better battery life, and improved performance
            on slower devices and networks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background: #f9fafb; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #8b5cf6;">
          <h4 style="color: #6b21a8; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">üîç SEO Friendly</h4>
          <p style="color: #4b5563;">
            Search engines can crawl your static content immediately. No need for complex
            server-side rendering or hydration strategies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem;">Loading Strategies</h3>

      <div class="demo-grid" style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        <div class="demo-card">
          <h4>client:load</h4>
          <p>Loads immediately when the page loads. Use for critical interactive elements like navigation or primary CTAs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="demo-card">
          <h4>client:idle</h4>
          <p>Loads when the browser is idle. Perfect for secondary features like analytics or non-critical widgets.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="demo-card">
          <h4>client:visible</h4>
          <p>Loads when the element becomes visible. Great for below-the-fold content like comments or related articles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <pre class="code-block"><code>
&lt;!-- Critical interactive element --&gt;
&lt;island src="./Navigation.plk" client:load&gt;
  &lt;nav&gt;Loading navigation...&lt;/nav&gt;
&lt;/island&gt;

&lt;!-- Secondary feature --&gt;
&lt;island src="./Analytics.plk" client:idle&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;Loading analytics...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/island&gt;

&lt;!-- Below-the-fold content --&gt;
&lt;island src="./Comments.plk" client:visible&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;Loading comments...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/island&gt;
      </code></pre>

      <div style="background: #f0f9ff; border: 1px solid #0ea5e9; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h3 style="color: #0c4a6e; margin-bottom: 1rem;">When to Use Islands</h3>
        <ul style="color: #075985; margin-left: 1.5rem;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Interactive forms</strong> - Real-time validation, dynamic fields</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Search components</strong> - Autocomplete, filtering, suggestions</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Data visualization</strong> - Charts, graphs, interactive maps</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Media players</strong> - Video players, audio controls</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Widgets</strong> - Calculators, converters, tools</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Comments systems</strong> - Real-time updates, moderation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

